This paper deals with safe robot mission planning, which is a core problem in robotics. The paper focuses on uncertain dynamical environments, which is a common challenge in robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses probabilistic models and Monte Carlo methods, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also deals with safety, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) for robotics applications.
